creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 156 by Various.
Read in English by Librivox volunteers. This is a collection of 29 poems for May 2016: At a Solemn Music, by John Milton The Bozhur Flower, by Milan Rakić Faith is a Fine Invention, by Emily Dickinson Father and Child, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox Frankincense and Myrrh, by Amy Lowell The Indian's Bride, by Edward Coote Pinkney In Kensington Gardens, by Arthur Symons Joys of Memory, by Thomas Hardy The Last Word, by Matthew Arnold The Love Song of J. Alfred Prufrock, by T. S. Eliot The Manual System, by Carl Sandburg May Wind, by Sara Teasdale The Men Who Come Behind, by Henry Lawson Miss Marie Corelli, by Harry Graham The Old Church, by William Byron Forbush Omar Khayyam, by Harry Graham Phantasmagoria, by Lewis Carroll Porphyria's Lover, by Robert Browning Purple Clover, by Emily Dickinson Sexagenarius Loquitur, by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle The Shooting of Dan McGrew, by Robert W. Service Song of Contraries, by Jordi de Sant Jordi The Terrors of Guilt, by Matilda Betham To a Lady on Her Passion for Old China, by John Gay Twilight, by Paul Bloomfield The Voyager's song, by Edward Coote Pinkney We Sat at the Window, by Thomas Hardy The Widow's song, by Edward Coote Pinkney Woman Walking, by William Carlos Williams
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
